            "type": "text",
            "text": "Choosing the Threshold"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A threshold of 0.75–0.85 is a reasonable starting point for English prose. Lower values (0.60–0.70) produce larger chunks that span multiple subtopics; higher values (0.85–0.95) produce very fine-grained chunks. Tune by inspecting split points on a sample document: the split should land between paragraphs on distinct topics, not within a cohesive argument."
          }
        ]
      },
