            "text": "Choose fixed-size chunking for speed and simplicity when document structure is uniform. Use recursive chunking for prose and markdown — it respects paragraph and sentence boundaries without embedding overhead. Use semantic chunking for long documents with distinct topic sections where retrieval precision matters most. In all cases, store chunk metadata (doc_id, source, page) alongside the vector so Claude can cite the source accurately. Start with 400 tokens and 60 token overlap as a baseline and adjust based on retrieval evaluation metrics."
